          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1706614064445-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel your <strong>ginger</strong> (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon), then peel your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Slice your <strong>red</strong> <strong>chilli[es]</strong> in half and scrape the seeds out with a spoon, and chop your <strong>coriander</strong> roughly, reserving some leaves for garnish</p><p>Add the<strong> ginger</strong>,<strong> garlic</strong>, <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>red chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>chopped coriander</strong> to a <strong>food processor</strong> with 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp] </span>[4 tbsp] </span><strong>water</strong> and blitz until smooth – this is your <strong>Thai green curry paste</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-1706624111690-x200.jpg",
